# InsightOps Access Visualizer — Project Context

## What This Project Does
InsightOps is a fullstack TypeScript tool that visualizes Azure DevOps access control.
It fetches identity graphs, permission ACLs, and group memberships via Azure DevOps REST APIs,
then renders them as an interactive node-graph so users can trace exactly WHY a user
has (or does not have) access to a repository.

## Monorepo Structure
insightops-access-visualizer/
├── apps/
│   ├── backend/   → Node.js + Express + TypeScript
│   └── frontend/  → React 18 + TypeScript + Vite
├── .cursor/rules/
└── docs/

## Tech Stack — Do Not Deviate
- Package manager / runtime: Bun (always use `bun add`, never `npm install`)
- Backend: Node.js, Express, TypeScript (strict), Zod, Axios
- Frontend: React 18, TypeScript (strict), Vite, Tailwind CSS v3
- Graph UI: @xyflow/react (react-flow v12)
- Layout: @dagrejs/dagre
- State: Zustand v4
- Data fetching: @tanstack/react-query v5
- Validation everywhere: Zod v3

## Org-First Data Model
Azure DevOps PAT tokens are org-scoped. The app ALWAYS:
1. Fetches the full list of projects for the org first
2. Lets the user select one or more projects
3. Scopes all downstream API calls to the selected project(s)
There is NO hardcoded default project anywhere in the codebase.

## Key Architectural Decisions
- All Azure DevOps API calls are centralized in `AzureDevOpsClient` class
- All env vars accessed ONLY via `src/config/env.ts` (Zod-validated)
- All AzDO API responses parsed with Zod schemas before use
- In-memory cache wraps every AzDO service call with configurable TTL
- Identity descriptor resolution is mandatory before correlating Graph ↔ Security ACL data
- Bitmask decoding: `(bitmask & bit) === bit` — defined in `azdo.constants.ts`